      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MY LITTLE BO (9) was good when beaten only 3.7m in a stronger race here last start. Had been racing very well with a string of wins or placings prior including a second in the Listed Riverina Championships Final two back. Draws on the back row but her form reads strongly for this. INTRUSION (8) drew wide and went back last start then worked home with a long sustained run to score by nearly 12 metres at this circuit and distance last time out. Shouldn't spend a penny from this draw and the sprint lane may come in handy. Big chance to land the prize again. SOAP AND BUBBLES (7) was fifth as favourite last start but had looked close to a win when runner-up in her previous two outings. Draws wide but must be considered. A good draw gives SEA FURY NZ (2) his chance to continue the consistent form.",
